To establish a strong digital presence over the next four years at VIT Bhopal, I have selected GitHub, LinkedIn, and Stack Overflow as my primary professional platforms. 
Each serves a distinct purpose in my journey as a CSE student.

GitHub is my central repository for version control and project management. 
I use it to host my code, such as the Japanese flashcard app and my BGMI tournament manager.
Over the next four years, I plan to build a consistent "contribution graph" by documenting my academic labs and personal projects, eventually contributing to open-source software to demonstrate my technical proficiency to recruiters.

LinkedIn acts as my professional storefront. It is where I connect with mentors, peers, and industry leaders. I use it to showcase my achievements and certifications.
Moving forward, I will use it to share updates on my learning milestones in Python and C++, ensuring my profile is optimized for internship opportunities by my third year.

Stack Overflow is my go-to for technical problem-solving.
It allows me to troubleshoot complex coding errors and engage with the global developer community.
My goal is to transition from a passive seeker of answers to an active contributor, building a reputation score that reflects my expertise and willingness to help others.
